Xiaomi has launched its new Black Shark 2 smartphone, which sports unique features aimed at mobile gaming enthusiasts. The smartphone features a pressure-sensitive 6.39-inch AMOLED display which allows players to vary their inputs depending on how hard they press down on the screen. The company has built an in-screen fingerprint scanner into the device, and the smartphone also boasts a 4,000mAh battery and 27W fast-charging support. Xiaomi’s Black Shark 2 has a striking, aggressive chassis design aimed at the gaming market, but it still includes premium features like a bezel-less display and dual-camera system on the back of the device. The Black Shark 2 is available in China and is priced from ¥3,199 (around R6,875).